This paper deals with predicting personality traits from smartphone data, which falls under the category of computational social science (cs.CY). The paper also involves data analysis and machine learning techniques, which could potentially fall under sub-categories such as cs.SI (social and information networks), cs.SD (software engineering), and cs.CL (computation and language). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of previous studies, which could be relevant to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
